The draw for the U17 and U20 AFCONs will be staged this evening for both the Golden Eaglets and the Flying Eagles to know their first round foes in their respective competitions. The Golden Eaglets won the WAFU B U17 qualifiers in Ghana, while the Flying Eagles topped the qualifiers in Niger. The U17 AFCON will be hosted by Algeria, while the U20 AFCON will be played in Egypt with both competitions also serving as qualifiers for their respective World Cups next year.